100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On January 21, 1926, the British Parliament debated the future of the coal industry, facing pressure from miners over pay and working conditions. In the United States, the ongoing trial of the notorious gangster Al Capone continued to capture public attention amid rising concerns over organized crime. Meanwhile, the League of Nations held discussions in Geneva regarding disarmament efforts, reflecting the global desire for lasting peace following the devastation of the Great War.
